msgid "Additional Notes on General Windows Keystrokes"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:18-1
msgid "Get Help (F1)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:19-1
msgid "This keystroke brings up help for the active application."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:20-1
msgid "Switch between Open Applications (ALT+TAB)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:21-1
msgid ""
"If pressed once, this keystroke switches focus to the open application that "
"was last used prior to the current application being used. To cycle through "
"open applications to find the one you want, hold down <b>ALT</b> and press "
"and release <b>TAB</b> until you find it. Then release both keys. The "
"<b>ALT+TAB</b> \"switch to\" order is determined by the order in which "
"applications have last been used, not by the order in which they were "
"originally opened."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:22-1
msgid "Open the Shortcut Menu (APPLICATION KEY or SHIFT+F10)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:23-1
msgid ""
"This keystroke brings up a shortcut menu (context menu) for the item that "
"has the PC Cursor focus."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:24-1
msgid "Minimize all Windows (WINDOWS KEY+M)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:25-1
msgid ""
"Some dialog boxes cannot be minimized. Using this keystroke with a dialog "
"box of this type open can result in the system focus being on the Windows "
"Desktop with most of the Desktop covered by the dialog box - preventing JAWS "
"from reading the desktop items properly."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:26-1
msgid "Move to First Item on the Taskbar (WINDOWS KEY+TAB)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cgeneral_windows_keystrokes-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:27-1
msgid ""
"This keystroke moves focus to the first item on the taskbar, but does not "
"open that application."
msgstr ""

